    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "***Sentiment Analysis***\n",
        "\n",
        "Each poem text was passed to the `polarity_scores()` function of the SentimentIntensityAnalyzer, which returns a dictionary containing four sentiment metrics:\n",
        "1. Positive score (pos): proportion of the text associated with positive sentiment\n",
        "2. Negative score (neg): proportion associated with negative sentiment\n",
        "3. Neutral score (neu): proportion considered neutral\n",
        "4. Compound score: a normalized, aggregated sentiment score ranging from −1 (most negative) to +1 (most positive)\n",
        "\n",
        "> *Note: For analytical purposes, the compound score was used as the primary indicator of overall sentiment polarity, as it summarizes the combined valence of the text.*"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "K_c3BLRAeT66"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "sia = SentimentIntensityAnalyzer()\n",
        "\n",
        "df['sentiment_scores'] = df['Text'].apply(lambda x: sia.polarity_scores(str(x)))\n",
        "df['compound'] = df['sentiment_scores'].apply(lambda x: x['compound'])"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "kjUI3WU0ecor"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        ">*To facilitate interpretation, compound scores were converted into categorical sentiment labels. Following standard VADER conventions, poems were classified according to the following thresholds:*\n",
        ">* *compound ≥ 0.05 → positive sentiment*\n",
        ">* *compound ≤ −0.05 → negative sentiment*\n",
        ">* *−0.05 < compound < 0.05 → neutral sentiment*"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ClMPgFC8jXcV"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "def classify_sentiment(score):\n",
        "    if score >= 0.05:\n",
        "        return \"Positive\"\n",
        "    elif score <= -0.05:\n",
        "        return \"Negative\"\n",
        "    else:\n",
        "        return \"Neutral\"\n",
        "\n",
        "df['sentiment'] = df['compound'].apply(classify_sentiment)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "22C17cOXenrC"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
