      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "***Function to run LDA (Latent Dirichlet Allocation)***\n",
        "\n",
        "LDA first creates a dictionary from the tokenized poems, mapping each unique word to an ID. Here, the conditons have been set to filter out **extremely rare words** (appearing in fewer than two poems) and **overly common words** (appearing in more than 80% of poems) are removed to reduce noise in the model. This was decided after iterative trials.\n",
        "\n",
        "Next, each poem is converted into a bag-of-words (BoW) representation. Using this corpus, an LDA model is trained with a specified number of topics (specified later in **Model Training** step), iterating multiple times (here `15`) and using a fixed random seed (here `42`) to ensure reproducibility.\n",
        "\n",
        ">*Note: More onformation on LDA is available [here](https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/machine-learning/latent-dirichlet-allocation-and-topic-modelling/).*"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "sfYdMFMptASB"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "def run_lda(token_series, num_topics):\n",
        "\n",
        "    dictionary = corpora.Dictionary(token_series)\n",
        "\n",
        "    dictionary.filter_extremes(\n",
        "    no_below=2,   # word must appear in at least 2 poems\n",
        "    no_above=0.8  # remove words appearing in >80% of poems\n",
        "    )\n",
        "\n",
        "    corpus = [dictionary.doc2bow(text) for text in token_series]\n",
        "\n",
        "    lda_model = gensim.models.LdaModel(\n",
        "        corpus=corpus,\n",
        "        id2word=dictionary,\n",
        "        num_topics=num_topics,\n",
        "        passes=15,\n",
        "        random_state=42\n",
        "    )\n",
        "\n",
        "    return lda_model, corpus, dictionary"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
