      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "### **3. Computational Scansion** (using CMU Dictionary)\n",
        "This portion follows a rigorous [testing](https://colab.research.google.com/drive/1KvOHV5xf7E2W_kcpNOI9A4w1f0EF2WjR?usp=sharing) of 2 commonly used tools for phonological analysis, [**Prosodic**](https://pypi.org/project/prosodic/) and [**CMU Dictionary**](https://pypi.org/project/cmudict/).\n",
        "\n",
        "It was found that while the former \"*metrical parser [...] uses linguistic theory to 'scan' lines of verse for their rhythm and meter[,]*\" it suffers from inflation of syllable counts and naturally of stress evaluation.\n",
        "\n",
        "Thus the latter, which \"*provides a mapping orthographic/phonetic for English words in their North American pronunciations*\" is used for the largescale prosody, as it was found to be more exhaustive in the syllable counting.\n",
        "\n",
        "Nonetheless, the Prosodic GUI was used for computational scansion of the poems selected for the close reading poems, and more information on it is included within the thesis proper.\n",
        "\n",
        ">*Note: Continuing from the previous analysis, certain steps have been skipped for redundancy, including but not limited to the package installation and importing.*"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "KZzh76o6pc-c"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "***Installing and Importing Libraries***"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "EkDexR8roY2J"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "nltk.download(\"cmudict\")\n",
        "\n",
        "from nltk.corpus import cmudict\n",
        "d = cmudict.dict()"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "collapsed": true,
        "id": "h-f0FyJ3oVGA",
