    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "***Rhyme Evaluation***\n",
        "\n",
        "This was done following the practice in the [Scansion Tool Test](https://colab.research.google.com/drive/1KvOHV5xf7E2W_kcpNOI9A4w1f0EF2WjR?usp=sharing).\n",
        "\n",
        ">*Note: Some steps were removed for redundancy, including but not limited to the installing and importing of packages needed for this phase.*"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "07AUimSryCcf"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "*Function to get Rhyme Sound*"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Ul9d8pZXRdX-"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "def rhyme_part(word):\n",
        "    word = word.lower()\n",
        "\n",
        "    if word not in d:\n",
        "        return None\n",
        "\n",
        "    pronunciation = d[word][0]\n",
        "\n",
        "    for i in range(len(pronunciation)-1, -1, -1):\n",
        "        if pronunciation[i][-1].isdigit():\n",
        "            return tuple(pronunciation[i:])"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "MvL4pp_3Qu_R"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "*Function to get Last Word of Each Line*"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "IVFhj8bmRooY"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "def get_last_words(poem):\n",
        "\n",
        "    lines = poem.split(\"\\n\") # Splitting poem into lines\n",
        "    last_words = []\n",
        "\n",
        "    for line in lines:\n",
        "        words = re.findall(r\"[a-zA-Z']+\", line.lower())\n",
        "        if words:\n",
        "            last_words.append(words[-1])\n",
        "\n",
        "    return last_words"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Dh4fGNWcRuTC"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "*Function to get Rhyme Scheme*"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "15MKFuwVRxzW"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        ">*Some poems are way over 26 lines long which mean the traditional alphabet tagging of lines (A, B, C, etc.) to check rhyme will not work, thus this is solved by iterating through the alphabet to get AA, AB, AC and so on.*"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "BtSc2YvRT6lV"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import string\n",
        "\n",
        "def label_generator():\n",
        "\n",
        "    letters = string.ascii_uppercase\n",
        "    n = 1\n",
        "\n",
        "    while True:\n",
        "        for comb in __import__(\"itertools\").product(letters, repeat=n):\n",
        "            yield \"\".join(comb)\n",
        "        n += 1"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "apRiBEx1T47E"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "> *The function below checks whether a poem contains systematic rhyme and, if so, generates its rhyme scheme, and to do so there are some conditions implemented after iterative trials:*\n",
        ">\n",
        ">1. *The frequency of each rhyme sound (found with `rhyme_part()`) is calculated and only rhyme sounds that occur at least **twice** are retained, since a rhyme must appear at least more than once to constitute anything resembling a pattern. If no rhyme sounds repeat, the function concludes that the poem does not contain meaningful rhyme and returns `None`.*\n",
        ">\n",
        ">2. *To avoid detecting accidental matches, the proportion of rhyming lines that rhyme is calculated by dividing the total number of rhyming lines by the total number of lines in the poem, producing a rhyme ratio. If the ratio is* <***15%***, *the poem is treated as **free verse** and the function again returns `None`.*\n",
        ">\n",
        ">3. *If a sufficient proportion of lines rhyme, the function constructs a **rhyme scheme**. Each distinct rhyme sound is assigned a letter/letter-combination generated by the `label_generator()`, defined just before this step. Lines that contain rhyme sounds belonging to the repeated set receive the corresponding label, while lines that do not participate in rhyme are marked with an underscore (_).*\n",
        ">\n",
        ">*The final result is returned as a string representing the poem’s rhyme scheme, where repeated letters indicate rhyming lines and underscores denote unrhymed lines.*"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "qyzoIfH1YJyQ"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "def rhyme_scheme(poem, min_ratio=0.15): # Setting the threshold for proportion of rhyming lines as 15%\n",
        "\n",
        "    last_words = get_last_words(poem)\n",
        "    rhymes = [rhyme_part(w) for w in last_words if rhyme_part(w)]\n",
        "\n",
        "    counts = Counter(rhymes)\n",
        "\n",
        "    repeated = {r:c for r,c in counts.items() if c >= 2} # Keeping only rhymes that appear at least twice, a heuristic minimum\n",
        "\n",
        "    if not repeated:\n",
        "        return None\n",
        "\n",
        "    rhyming_lines = sum(repeated.values()) # Checking proportion of rhyming lines\n",
        "    ratio = rhyming_lines / len(last_words)\n",
        "\n",
        "    if ratio < min_ratio:\n",
        "        return None\n",
        "\n",
        "    labels = label_generator()  # Building scheme only for meaningful rhymes\n",
        "    rhyme_map = {}\n",
        "    scheme = []\n",
        "\n",
        "    for w in last_words:\n",
        "\n",
        "        r = rhyme_part(w)\n",
        "\n",
        "        if r not in repeated:\n",
        "            scheme.append(\"_\")   # Unrhymed line\n",
        "            continue\n",
        "\n",
        "        if r not in rhyme_map:\n",
        "            rhyme_map[r] = next(labels)\n",
        "\n",
        "        scheme.append(rhyme_map[r])\n",
        "\n",
        "    return \"\".join(scheme)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "JcWFtYc7R5hZ"
      },
