    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "***Refrain***\n",
        "\n",
        "This is \"[a] phrase or line repeated at intervals within a poem, especially at the end of a stanza.\" (Poetry Foundation) Eg: Walt Whitman's \"O Captain! My Captain!\"\n",
        "\n",
        "However, for computation, there will be need to be affordances made, and as such any substantial repetition will be considered.\n",
        ">*Note: Certain package installations, importing, and df reading are skipped for redundancy.*"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "MLmTR6_NSupl"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        ">*Function to Detect Line Refrains*\n",
        ">\n",
        ">*This function cleans, following pre-processing convention, and counts repeating lines.*"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "2bHIyrCMXzPb"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "def line_refrains(poem):\n",
        "\n",
        "    lines = poem.split(\"\\n\") # Splitting poem into lines\n",
        "\n",
        "    clean = [\n",
        "        re.sub(r\"[^\\w\\s]\", \"\", l.lower()).strip()\n",
        "        for l in lines if l.strip()\n",
        "    ]\n",
        "\n",
        "    counts = Counter(clean)\n",
        "\n",
        "    return {l:c for l,c in counts.items() if c >= 2}"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "QdKhjVeBSz9H"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        ">*Function to Detect Phrase Refrains*\n",
        ">\n",
        ">*This will be done using [n-grams](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/N-gram) on phrases with 2-6 words. Of course, this is a researcher decision but follows iterative practice and avoids overemphasis on single words that may be repeated sporadically.*\n",
        ">\n",
        ">*The `CountVectorizer()` from [sklearn](https://scikit-learn.org/stable/) is used to extract the phrases. Single-word repetitions are excluded to avoid noise from common words. After extracting the phrases, their frequencies are counted, and phrases that occur thrice or more are treated as refrain-like repetitions.*\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "C6lAoKZqYEIw"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "from sklearn.feature_extraction.text import CountVectorizer\n",
        "\n",
        "def phrase_refrains(poem):\n",
        "\n",
        "    lines = [l.strip() for l in poem.split(\"\\n\") if l.strip()]\n",
        "\n",
        "    vectorizer = CountVectorizer(\n",
        "        ngram_range=(2,6), # Phrases of 2–6 words\n",
        "        lowercase=True, # Lowercasing\n",
        "        stop_words='english' # Stopword removal\n",
        "    )\n",
        "\n",
        "    X = vectorizer.fit_transform(lines) # Detecting phrases and how many times they appear\n",
        "\n",
        "    freqs = X.sum(axis=0).A1 # Total counts for each phrase across poem\n",
        "    terms = vectorizer.get_feature_names_out() # Extracts detected phrases\n",
        "\n",
        "    phrases = dict(zip(terms, freqs))\n",
        "\n",
        "    return {p:c for p,c in phrases.items() if c >= 3} # Phrases thrice or more"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "tPOdeTDzYIeN"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        ">*Combining Functions*"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "9ZOWBfIHYlis"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "def detect_refrains(poem):\n",
        "\n",
        "    lines = line_refrains(poem)\n",
        "    phrases = phrase_refrains(poem)\n",
        "\n",
        "    return {\n",
        "        \"line_refrains\": lines,\n",
        "        \"phrase_refrains\": phrases\n",
        "    }"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ezboi63PYmlh"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        ">*Applying Function*"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "H-0izwx2Yv7i"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "df[\"refrains\"] = df[\"Text\"].apply(detect_refrains) # The results are stored in new column \"refrains\""
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "OW8VgyvHYzpt"
      },
