    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "***Enjambment***\n",
        "\n",
        "This happens when poem line continues onto the next without being end-stopped. Eg: Lord Tennyson's \"In Memoriam\" Canto 27."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "gKur8xmjiU4h"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        ">*Function to Check Punctuation*\n",
        ">\n",
        ">*Before checking for enjambment, it should be noted that in social media poetry some poems are stylised to not have any punctuations, so it would be irrational to simply consider the absence of them as an enjambment marker. Instead, if a poem does have punctuations but not in each line, only then it will be flagged as enjambed.*"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "AwhHsYCRzMCQ"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "def has_endstops(poem):\n",
        "\n",
        "    lines = [l.strip() for l in poem.split(\"\\n\") if l.strip()] # Splitting into lines\n",
        "\n",
        "    punct_lines = sum(1 for l in lines if re.search(r\"[.!?;:,]$\", l))# Counting lines ending with punctuation\n",
        "\n",
        "    return punct_lines > 0  # Returns only end-stopped lines"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Qb2gEvdbzPYT"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        ">*Filtering Poems for Enjambent Review*\n",
        ">\n",
        ">*All the poems that have absolutely no end-stopped lines are dropped*"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "6IiLq6qoy4Jm"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "df['has_endstop'] = df['Text'].apply(has_endstops)\n",
        "\n",
        "poems_for_enjambment = df[df['has_endstop']]"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "NI78NMN4zH25"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        ">*Function to find Enjambment*\n",
        ">\n",
        ">*For the poems filtered, the lines not end-stopped are considered to be enjambed, while ignoring the last line as it can not flow into any further lines.*"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "_h-936vHyxK2"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "def count_enjambed_lines(poem):\n",
        "\n",
        "    lines = [l.strip() for l in poem.split(\"\\n\") if l.strip()]\n",
        "\n",
        "    return sum(1 for line in lines[:-1] if not re.search(r\"[.!?;:,]$\", line)) # Ignoring last line"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "wwTH6I-hyw3r"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
