    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        ">*Extracting Similes for the Poems Closely Read*\n",
        ">\n",
        ">*While the simile ratio provides a broad measure of how frequently comparative language appears, it can be a rather reductive way to studying this device. Thus selected poems were extracted as examples that can be then cross-verified.*"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "DoM-snkQ87Ls"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "target_poems = [\"A28\", \"A37\", \"C01\", \"C04\", \"L04\", \"L11\"]\n",
        "\n",
        "selected = df[df['Poem ID'].isin(target_poems)]"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "eq3SFjdo9Jcv"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        ">*Function to Extract Simile Lines from Selected Poems*"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "_IJL-e7CvfK7"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "def extract_simile_lines(text):\n",
        "    lines = text.lower().split(\"\\n\") # Lowercasing and splitting poem into lines\n",
        "    return [line for line in lines if any(re.search(p, line) for p in patterns)]\n",
        "\n",
        "df['Simile_Examples'] = df['Text'].apply(extract_simile_lines)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "NVsYgY_v8S-I"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        ">*Applying the Function*"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "vP03YPmCvuCK"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "for _, row in selected.iterrows():\n",
        "    print(f\"\\nPoem {row['Poem ID']} — {row['Title']}\")\n",
        "    print(\"-\" * 40)\n",
        "\n",
        "    for line in row['Simile_Examples']:\n",
        "        print(line)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "UPG0Ofhf9M2J",
        "outputId": "a36b2a3b-2d71-457f-b01e-a1124749db49"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
