    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "***Metaphor***\n",
        "\n",
        "A metaphor is an implicit comparison between different things. It is one of the most commonly used devices across any poetic format including many cantos of Lord Tennyson's \"In Memoriam.\"\n",
        "\n",
        ">*Note: To override the `df` thus far, the CSV has been read again as `df` and the categegorisation has been done anew.*"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "-7JP28yN-_SD"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        ">*Installing & Importing Packages*\n",
        ">\n",
        ">*This stage installs [Transformers](https://pypi.org/project/transformers/) and [Torch](https://pypi.org/project/torch/) to use advanced language models like RoBERTa which allows the actual metaphor detection has been done using [RoBERTa](https://huggingface.co/docs/transformers/en/model_doc/roberta). Specifically, this phase uses [lwachowiak/Metaphor-Detection-XLMR](https://huggingface.co/lwachowiak/Metaphor-Detection-XLMR) reliant on RoBERTa.*"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "mhF3iuFsBoZL"
      }
    },
